Name: Jericho

Name: Dexter
Information: By day, mild-mannered Dexter is a blood-spatter analyst for the Miami police. But at night, he is a serial killer who only targets other murderers.

Name: We Are Marshall
Information: When a plane crash claims the lives of members of the Marshall University football team and some of its fans, the team's new coach and his surviving players try to keep the football program alive.

Name: Friday Night Lights
Information: A drama that follows the lives of the Dillon Panthers, one of the nation's best high school football teams, and their head coach Eric Taylor.

Name: Letters from Iwo Jima
Information: The story of the battle of Iwo Jima between the United States and Imperial Japan during World War II, as told from the perspective of the Japanese who fought it.

Name: An Inconvenient Truth
Directors_stars: ['Davis Guggenheim', 'Al Gore', 'Billy West', 'George Bush', 'George W. Bush']
Information: Filmmaker Davis Guggenheim follows Al Gore on the lecture circuit, as the former presidential candidate campaigns to raise public awareness of the dangers of global warming and calls for immediate action to curb its destructive effects on the environment.

Name: 30 Rock
Information: Liz Lemon (Tina Fey), head writer of the sketch comedy show "TGS with Tracy Jordan", must deal with an arrogant new boss and a crazy new star, all while trying to run a successful television show without losing her mind.

Name: Jackass Number Two
Information: Chris Pontius, Johnny Knoxville, Steve-O, Bam Margera, and the whole crew return to the screen to raise the stakes higher than ever before.

Name: Psych
Information: A novice sleuth is hired by the Police after he cons them into thinking he has psychic powers which help solve crimes. With the assistance of his reluctant best friend, the duo take on a series of complicated cases.

Name: Saw III
Directors_stars: ['Darren Lynn Bousman', 'Tobin Bell', 'Shawnee Smith', 'Angus Macfadyen', 'Bahar Soomekh']
Information: Jigsaw abducts a doctor in order to keep himself alive while he watches his new apprentice put an unlucky citizen named Jeff through a brutal test.

Name: The IT Crowd
Information: The comedic misadventures of Roy, Moss and their grifting supervisor Jen, a rag-tag team of IT support workers at a large corporation headed by a hotheaded yuppie.

Name: Beerfest
Information: Two brothers travel to Germany for Oktoberfest, only to stumble upon a secret, centuries-old competition described as a "Fight Club" with beer games.

Name: The Prestige
Information: After a tragic accident, two stage magicians engage in a battle to create the ultimate illusion while sacrificing everything they have to outwit each other.

Name: This Is England
Information: A young boy becomes friends with a gang of skinheads. Friends soon become like family, and relationships will be pushed to the very limit.

Name: Crank
Directors_stars: ['Mark Neveldine', 'Brian Taylor', 'Jason Statham', 'Amy Smart', 'Carlos Sanz', 'Jose Pablo Cantillo']
Information: Professional assassin Chev Chelios learns his rival has injected him with a poison that will kill him if his heart rate drops.

Name: Rocky Balboa
Information: Thirty years after the ring of the first bell, Rocky Balboa comes out of retirement and dons his gloves for his final fight against the reigning heavyweight champ Mason 'The Line' Dixon.

Name: Night at the Museum
Directors_stars: ['Shawn Levy', 'Ben Stiller', 'Carla Gugino', 'Ricky Gervais', 'Dick Van Dyke']
Information: A newly recruited night security guard at the Museum of Natural History discovers that an ancient curse causes the animals and exhibits on display to come to life and wreak havoc.

Name: Wristcutters: A Love Story
Information: A film set in a strange afterlife way station that has been reserved for people who have committed suicide.

Name: Smokin' Aces
Information: When a Las Vegas performer-turned-snitch named Buddy Israel decides to turn state's evidence and testify against the mob, it seems that a whole lot of people would like to make sure he's no longer breathing.

Name: United 93
Directors_stars: ['Paul Greengrass', 'David Alan Basche', 'Olivia Thirlby', 'Liza Colón-Zayas', 'J.J. Johnson']
Information: A real-time account of the events on United Flight 93, one of the planes hijacked on September 11th, 2001 that crashed near Shanksville, Pennsylvania when passengers foiled the terrorist plot.

Name: Penelope
Directors_stars: ['Mark Palansky', 'Christina Ricci', 'James McAvoy', 'Reese Witherspoon', 'Richard E. Grant']
Information: A modern romantic tale about a young aristocratic heiress born under a curse that can only be broken when she finds true love with "one who will accept her as one of their own."

Name: Apocalypto
Directors_stars: ['Mel Gibson', 'Gerardo Taracena', 'Raoul Max Trujillo', 'Dalia Hernández', 'Rudy Youngblood']
Information: As the Mayan kingdom faces its decline, a young man is taken on a perilous journey to a world ruled by fear and oppression.

Name: World Trade Center
Information: Two Port Authority police officers become trapped under the rubble of the World Trade Center.

Name: Gwoemul
Directors_stars: ['Bong Joon Ho', 'Kang-ho Song', 'Hee-Bong Byun', 'Hae-il Park', 'Doona Bae']
Information: A monster emerges from Seoul's Han River and begins attacking people. One victim's loving family does what it can to rescue her from its clutches.

Name: Half Nelson
Information: An inner-city junior high school teacher with a drug habit forms an unlikely friendship with one of his students after she discovers his secret.

Name: The Omen
Information: An American official realizes that his young son may literally be the Devil incarnate.

Name: Date Movie
Directors_stars: ['Aaron Seltzer', 'Jason Friedberg', 'Alyson Hannigan', 'Adam Campbell', 'Fred Willard', 'Jennifer Coolidge']
Information: Spoof of romantic comedies which focuses on a man, his crush, his parents, and her father.

Name: My Super Ex-Girlfriend
Information: When a regular guy dumps a superhero for her neediness, she uses her powers to make his life a living hell.

Name: Notes on a Scandal
Information: A veteran high school teacher befriends a younger art teacher, who is having an affair with one of her fifteen-year-old students. However, her intentions with this new "friend" also go well beyond a platonic friendship.

Name: The Fast and the Furious: Tokyo Drift
Directors_stars: ['Justin Lin', 'Lucas Black', 'Zachery Ty Bryan', 'Shad Moss', 'Damien Marzette']
Information: A teenager becomes a major competitor in the world of drift racing after moving in with his father in Tokyo to avoid a jail sentence in America.

Name: You, Me and Dupree
Directors_stars: ['Anthony Russo', 'Joe Russo', 'Kate Hudson', 'Owen Wilson', 'Matt Dillon', 'Michael Douglas']
Information: A best man (Wilson) stays on as a houseguest with the newlyweds, much to the couple's annoyance.

Name: Step Up
Information: Tyler Gage receives the opportunity of a lifetime after vandalizing a performing arts school, gaining him the chance to earn a scholarship and dance with an up and coming dancer, Nora.

Name: Rescue Dawn
Information: A U.S. fighter pilot's epic struggle of survival after being shot down on a mission over Laos during the Vietnam War.

Name: Black Snake Moan
Directors_stars: ['Craig Brewer', 'Christina Ricci', 'Samuel L. Jackson', 'Justin Timberlake', 'S. Epatha Merkerson']
Information: A God-fearing bluesman takes to a wild young woman who, as a victim of childhood sexual abuse, looks everywhere for love, never quite finding it.

Name: Inland Empire
Information: As an actress begins to adopt the persona of her character in a film, her world becomes nightmarish and surreal.

Name: The Fall
Information: In a hospital on the outskirts of 1920s Los Angeles, an injured stuntman begins to tell a fellow patient, a little girl with a broken arm, a fantastic story of five mythical heroes. Thanks to his fractured state of mind and her vivid imagination, the line between fiction and reality blurs as the tale advances.

Name: Cashback
Information: After a painful breakup, Ben develops insomnia. To kill time, he starts working the late night shift at the local supermarket, where his artistic imagination runs wild.

Name: The Devil Wears Prada
Information: A smart but sensible new graduate lands a job as an assistant to Miranda Priestly, the demanding editor-in-chief of a high fashion magazine.

Name: The Holiday
Information: Two women troubled with guy-problems swap homes in each other's countries, where they each meet a local guy and fall in love.

Name: Scoop
Information: An American journalism student in London scoops a big story, and begins an affair with an aristocrat as the incident unfurls.

Name: Nacho Libre
Directors_stars: ['Jared Hess', 'Jack Black', 'Ana de la Reguera', 'Héctor Jiménez', 'Darius Rose']
Information: Berated all his life by those around him, a monk follows his dream and dons a mask to moonlight as a Luchador (Mexican wrestler).

Name: Pan's Labyrinth
Directors_stars: ['Guillermo del Toro', 'Ivana Baquero', 'Ariadna Gil', 'Sergi López', 'Maribel Verdú']
Information: In the Falangist Spain of 1944, the bookish young stepdaughter of a sadistic army officer escapes into an eerie but captivating fantasy world.

Name: Grandma's Boy
Information: A thirty-five-year-old video game tester has to move in with his grandma and her two old lady roommates.

Name: John Tucker Must Die
Information: Three ex-girlfriends of a serial cheater set up their former lover to fall for the new girl in town so they can watch him get his heart broken.

Name: The Last King of Scotland
Information: Based on the events of the brutal Ugandan dictator Idi Amin's regime as seen by his personal physician during the 1970s.

Name: She's the Man
Information: When her brother decides to ditch for a couple weeks, Viola heads over to his elite boarding school, disguised as him, and proceeds to fall for his school's star soccer player, and soon learns she's not the only one with romantic troubles.

Name: The Pursuit of Happyness
Information: A struggling salesman takes custody of his son as he's poised to begin a life-changing professional career.

Name: Inside Man
Information: A police detective, a bank robber, and a high-power broker enter high-stakes negotiations after the criminal's brilliant heist spirals into a hostage situation.

Name: The Hills Have Eyes
Directors_stars: ['Alexandre Aja', 'Ted Levine', 'Kathleen Quinlan', 'Dan Byrd', 'Emilie de Ravin']
Information: A family falls victim to a group of mutated cannibals in a desert far away from civilization.

Name: Deja Vu
Information: After a ferry is bombed in New Orleans, an A.T.F. agent joins a unique investigation using experimental surveillance technology to find the bomber, but soon finds himself becoming obsessed with one of the victims.

Name: Lady in the Water
Directors_stars: ['M. Night Shyamalan', 'Paul Giamatti', 'Bryce Dallas Howard', 'Jeffrey Wright', 'Bob Balaban']
Information: Apartment building superintendent Cleveland Heep rescues what he thinks is a young woman from the pool he maintains. When he discovers that she is actually a character from a bedtime story who is trying to make the journey back to her home, he works with his tenants to protect his new friend from the creatures that are determined to keep her in our world.

Name: The Break-Up
Directors_stars: ['Peyton Reed', 'Jennifer Aniston', 'Vince Vaughn', 'Jon Favreau', 'Joey Lauren Adams']
Information: In a bid to keep their luxurious condo from their significant other, a couple's break-up proceeds to get uglier and nastier by the moment.

Name: The Wicker Man
Information: A sheriff investigating the disappearance of a young girl from a small island discovers there's a larger mystery to solve among the island's secretive, neo-pagan community.

Name: Blood Diamond
Information: A fisherman, a smuggler, and a syndicate of businessmen match wits over the possession of a priceless diamond.

Name: 16 Blocks
Information: An aging alcoholic cop is assigned the task of escorting a witness from police custody to a courthouse 16 blocks away. There are, however, chaotic forces at work that prevent them from making it in one piece.

Name: Babel
Directors_stars: ['Alejandro G. Iñárritu', 'Brad Pitt', 'Cate Blanchett', 'Gael García Bernal', 'Mohamed Akhzam']
Information: Tragedy strikes a married couple on vacation in the Moroccan desert, touching off an interlocking story involving four different families.

Name: RV
Information: Bob Munro and his dysfunctional family rent an RV for a road trip to the Colorado Rockies, where they ultimately have to contend with a bizarre community of campers.

Name: Little Miss Sunshine
Directors_stars: ['Jonathan Dayton', 'Valerie Faris', 'Steve Carell', 'Toni Collette', 'Greg Kinnear', 'Abigail Breslin']
Information: A family determined to get their young daughter into the finals of a beauty pageant take a cross-country trip in their VW bus.

Name: Eragon
Information: In his homeland of Alagaesia, a farm boy happens upon a dragon's egg -- a discovery that leads him on a predestined journey where he realizes he's the one person who can defend his home against an evil king.

Name: The Painted Veil
Information: A British medical doctor fights a cholera epidemic in a small Chinese village, while being trapped at home in a loveless marriage to an unfaithful wife.

Name: Huo Yuan Jia
Information: A biography of Chinese Martial Arts Master Huo Yuanjia, who is the founder and spiritual guru of the Jin Wu Sports Federation.

Name: Invincible
Information: Based on the story of Vince Papale, a 30-year-old bartender from South Philadelphia who overcame long odds to play for the NFL's Philadelphia Eagles in 1976.

Name: The Illusionist
Information: In turn-of-the-century Vienna, a magician uses his abilities to secure the love of a woman far above his social standing.

Name: Dreamgirls
Information: A trio of black female soul singers cross over to the pop charts in the early 1960s, facing their own personal struggles along the way.

Name: Borat: Cultural Learnings of America for Make Benefit Glorious Nation of Kazakhstan
Information: Kazakh TV talking head Borat is dispatched to the United States to report on the greatest country in the world. With a documentary crew in tow, Borat becomes more interested in locating and marrying Pamela Anderson.

Name: Volver
Information: After her death, a mother returns to her home town in order to fix the situations she couldn't resolve during her life.

Name: Slither
Information: A small town is taken over by an alien plague, turning residents into zombies and all forms of mutant monsters.

Name: Ice Age: The Meltdown
Directors_stars: ['Carlos Saldanha', 'Ray Romano', 'John Leguizamo', 'Denis Leary', 'Seann William Scott']
Information: Manny, Sid, and Diego discover that the ice age is coming to an end, and join everybody for a journey to higher ground. On the trip, they discover that Manny, in fact, is not the last of the woolly mammoths.

Name: The Queen
Information: After the death of Princess Diana, Queen Elizabeth II struggles with her reaction to a sequence of events nobody could have predicted.

Name: Miami Vice
Information: Based on the 1980s TV action/drama, this update focuses on vice detectives Crockett and Tubbs as their respective personal and professional lives become dangerously intertwined.

Name: Failure to Launch
Directors_stars: ['Tom Dey', 'Matthew McConaughey', 'Sarah Jessica Parker', 'Kathy Bates', 'Terry Bradshaw']
Information: A thirty-something is still living with his parents until they hire an interventionist to help him graduate out of the house. That's when the fun begins.

Name: Alpha Dog
Information: Johnny and a couple pals kidnap Jake's 15-year-old brother, Zach, then assigns his buddy Frankie to be Zach's minder. They develop a brotherly friendship. Zach parties with his captors as things begin to spin out of control.

Name: Lucky Number Slevin
Information: A case of mistaken identity lands Slevin into the middle of a war being plotted by two of the city's most rival crime bosses: The Rabbi and The Boss. Slevin is under constant surveillance by relentless Detective Brikowski as well as the infamous assassin Goodkat and finds himself having to hatch his own ingenious plot to get them before they get him.

Name: Clerks II
Information: A calamity at Dante and Randal's shops sends them looking for new horizons - but they ultimately settle at the fast food empire Mooby's.

Name: Flushed Away
Directors_stars: ['David Bowers', 'Sam Fell', 'Hugh Jackman', 'Kate Winslet', 'Ian McKellen', 'Jean Reno']
Information: The story of an uptown rat that gets flushed down the toilet from his penthouse apartment, ending in the sewers of London, where he has to learn a whole new and different way of life.

Name: Marie Antoinette
Information: The retelling of France's iconic but ill-fated queen, Marie Antoinette. From her betrothal and marriage to Louis XVI at 15 to her reign as queen at 19 and to the end of her reign as queen, and ultimately the fall of Versailles.

Name: Gridiron Gang
Information: Teenagers at a juvenile detention center, under the leadership of their counselor, gain self-esteem by playing football together.

Name: The Texas Chainsaw Massacre: The Beginning
Information: Before being sent to serve in Vietnam, two brothers and their girlfriends take one last road trip, but when they get into an accident, a terrifying experience will take them to a secluded house of horrors, with a chainsaw-wielding killer.

Name: Stranger Than Fiction
Information: I.R.S. auditor Harold Crick suddenly finds himself the subject of narration only he can hear: narration that begins to affect his entire life, from his work, to his love-interest, to his death.

Name: Flags of Our Fathers
Information: The life stories of the six men who raised the flag at the Battle of Iwo Jima, a turning point in World War II.

Name: Snakes on a Plane
Directors_stars: ['David R. Ellis', 'Samuel L. Jackson', 'Julianna Margulies', 'Nathan Phillips', 'Rachel Blanchard']
Information: An F.B.I. Agent takes on a plane full of deadly venomous snakes, deliberately released to kill a witness being flown from Honolulu to Los Angeles to testify against a mob boss.
King Leonidas of Sparta and a force of 300 men fight the Persians at Thermopylae in 480 B.C.

Name: Talladega Nights: The Ballad of Ricky Bobby
Directors_stars: ['Adam McKay', 'Will Ferrell', 'John C. Reilly', 'Sacha Baron Cohen', 'Gary Cole']
Information: Number one NASCAR driver Ricky Bobby stays atop the heap thanks to a pact with his best friend and teammate, Cal Naughton, Jr. But when a French Formula One driver, makes his way up the ladder, Ricky Bobby's talent and devotion are put to the test.

Name: The Fountain
Directors_stars: ['Darren Aronofsky', 'Hugh Jackman', 'Rachel Weisz', 'Sean Patrick Thomas', 'Ellen Burstyn']
Information: As a modern-day scientist, Tommy is struggling with mortality, desperately searching for the medical breakthrough that will save the life of his cancer-stricken wife, Izzi.

Name: Final Destination 3
Directors_stars: ['James Wong', 'Mary Elizabeth Winstead', 'Ryan Merriman', 'Kris Lemche', 'Alexz Johnson']
Information: A student's premonition of a deadly roller coaster ride saves her life and a lucky few, but not from Death itself, which seeks out those who escaped their fate.

Name: The Lake House
Information: A lonely doctor, who once occupied an unusual lakeside house, begins exchanging love letters with its former resident, a frustrated architect. They must try to unravel the mystery behind their extraordinary romance before it's too late.

Name: Poseidon
Information: On New Year's Eve, the luxury ocean liner Poseidon capsizes after being swamped by a rogue wave. The survivors are left to fight for their lives as they attempt to escape the sinking ship.

Name: Firewall
Information: A security specialist is forced into robbing the bank that he's protecting, as a bid to pay off his family's ransom.

Name: The Departed
Information: An undercover cop and a mole in the police attempt to identify each other while infiltrating an Irish gang in South Boston.

Name: The Guardian
Information: A high school swim champion with a troubled past enrolls in the U.S. Coast Guard's "A" School, where legendary rescue swimmer Ben Randall teaches him some hard lessons about loss, love, and self-sacrifice.

Name: Rang De Basanti
Directors_stars: ['Rakeysh Omprakash Mehra', 'Aamir Khan', 'Soha Ali Khan', 'Siddharth', 'Sharman Joshi']
Information: The story of six young Indians who assist an English woman to film a documentary on the freedom fighters from their past, and the events that lead them to relive the long-forgotten saga of freedom.

Name: A Scanner Darkly
Directors_stars: ['Richard Linklater', 'Keanu Reeves', 'Winona Ryder', 'Robert Downey Jr.', 'Rory Cochrane']
Information: An undercover cop in a not-too-distant future becomes involved with a dangerous new drug and begins to lose his own identity as a result.

Name: The Lives of Others
Directors_stars: ['Florian Henckel von Donnersmarck', 'Ulrich Mühe', 'Martina Gedeck', 'Sebastian Koch', 'Ulrich Tukur']
Information: In 1984 East Berlin, an agent of the secret police, conducting surveillance on a writer and his lover, finds himself becoming increasingly absorbed by their lives.

Name: Running Scared
Information: A low-ranking thug is entrusted by his crime boss to dispose of a gun that killed corrupt cops, but things get out of control when the gun ends up in wrong hands.

Name: Little Children
Directors_stars: ['Todd Field', 'Kate Winslet', 'Jennifer Connelly', 'Patrick Wilson', 'Jackie Earle Haley']
Information: The lives of two lovelorn spouses from separate marriages, a registered sex offender, and a disgraced ex-police officer intersect as they struggle to resist their vulnerabilities and temptations in suburban Massachusetts.

Name: Underworld: Evolution
Information: Picking up directly from the previous movie, vampire warrior Selene and the half werewolf Michael hunt for clues to reveal the history of their races and the war between them.

Name: Paris, je t'aime
Directors_stars: ['Olivier Assayas', 'Frédéric Auburtin', 'Emmanuel Benbihy', 'Gurinder Chadha', 'Sylvain Chomet', 'Ethan Coen', 'Joel Coen', 'Isabel Coixet', 'Wes Craven', 'Alfonso Cuarón', 'Gérard Depardieu', 'Christopher Doyle', 'Richard LaGravenese', 'Vincenzo Natali', 'Alexander Payne', 'Bruno Podalydès', 'Walter Salles', 'Oliver Schmitz', 'Nobuhiro Suwa', 'Daniela Thomas', 'Tom Tykwer', 'Gus Van Sant', 'Juliette Binoche', 'Leonor Watling', 'Ludivine Sagnier', 'Fanny Ardant']
Information: Through the neighborhoods of Paris, love is veiled, revealed, imitated, sucked dry, reinvented and awakened.

Name: A Good Year
Information: A British investment broker inherits his uncle's chateau and vineyard in Provence, where he spent much of his childhood. He discovers a new laid-back lifestyle as he tries to renovate the estate to be sold.

Name: Open Season
Directors_stars: ['Roger Allers', 'Jill Culton', 'Anthony Stacchi', 'Ashton Kutcher', 'Martin Lawrence', 'Debra Messing', 'Gary Sinise']
Information: Boog, a domesticated 900lb. Grizzly bear, finds himself stranded in the woods 3 days before Open Season. Forced to rely on Elliot, a fast-talking mule deer, the two form an unlikely friendship and must quickly rally other forest animals if they are to form a rag-tag army against the hunters.

Name: Eight Below
Information: Brutal cold forces two Antarctic explorers to leave their team of sled dogs behind as they fend for their survival.

Name: Just My Luck
Information: Manhattanite Ashley is known to many as the luckiest woman around. After a chance encounter with a down-and-out young man, however, she realizes that she's swapped her fortune for his.

Name: Perfume: The Story of a Murderer
Information: Jean-Baptiste Grenouille, born with a superior olfactory sense, creates the world's finest perfume. His work, however, takes a dark turn as he searches for the ultimate scent.

Name: Click
Information: A workaholic architect finds a universal remote that allows him to fast-forward and rewind to different parts of his life. Complications arise when the remote starts to overrule his choices.

Name: Zwartboek
Directors_stars: ['Paul Verhoeven', 'Carice van Houten', 'Sebastian Koch', 'Thom Hoffman', 'Halina Reijn']
Information: In the Nazi-occupied Netherlands during World War II, a Jewish singer infiltrates the regional Gestapo headquarters for the Dutch resistance.

Name: The Black Dahlia
Directors_stars: ['Brian De Palma', 'Josh Hartnett', 'Aaron Eckhart', 'Scarlett Johansson', 'Hilary Swank']
Information: Two policemen see their personal and professional lives fall apart in the wake of the "Black Dahlia" Elizabeth Short murder investigation.

Name: Idiocracy
Information: Private Joe Bauers, the definition of "average American", is selected by the Pentagon to be the guinea pig for a top-secret hibernation program. Forgotten, he awakes five centuries in the future. He discovers a society so incredibly dumbed down that he's easily the most intelligent person alive.

Name: Monster House
Directors_stars: ['Gil Kenan', 'Mitchel Musso', 'Sam Lerner', 'Spencer Locke', 'Ryan Whitney Angel']
Information: Three teens discover that their neighbor's house is really a living, breathing, scary monster.

Name: Accepted
Information: A high school slacker who's rejected by every school he applies to opts to create his own institution of higher learning, the South Harmon Institute of Technology, on a rundown piece of property near his hometown.

Name: Silent Hill
Directors_stars: ['Christophe Gans', 'Radha Mitchell', 'Laurie Holden', 'Sean Bean', 'Deborah Kara Unger']
Information: A woman, Rose, goes in search for her adopted daughter within the confines of a strange, desolate town called Silent Hill.

Name: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Man's Chest
Information: Jack Sparrow races to recover the heart of Davy Jones to avoid enslaving his soul to Jones' service, as other friends and foes seek the heart for their own agenda as well.

Name: The Pink Panther
Information: Bumbling Inspector Clouseau must solve the murder of a famous soccer coach and find out who stole the infamous Pink Panther diamond.

Name: The Da Vinci Code
Information: A murder inside the Louvre, and clues in Da Vinci paintings, lead to the discovery of a religious mystery protected by a secret society for two thousand years, which could shake the foundations of Christianity.

Name: Casino Royale
Information: After earning 00 status and a licence to kill, Secret Agent James Bond sets out on his first mission as 007. Bond must defeat a private banker funding terrorists in a high-stakes game of poker at Casino Royale, Montenegro.

Name: X-Men: The Last Stand
Information: The human government develops a cure for mutations, and Jean Gray becomes a darker uncontrollable persona called the Phoenix who allies with Magneto, causing escalation into an all-out battle for the X-Men.

Name: Tristan + Isolde
Information: An affair between the second in line to Britain's throne and the princess of the feuding Irish spells doom for the young lovers.

Name: Ultraviolet
Information: A beautiful hæmophage infected with a virus that gives her superhuman powers has to protect a boy in a futuristic world, who is thought to be carrying antigens that would destroy all hæmophages.

Name: Happy Feet
Directors_stars: ['George Miller', 'Warren Coleman', 'Judy Morris', 'Elijah Wood', 'Brittany Murphy', 'Hugh Jackman', 'Robin Williams']
Information: Into the world of the Emperor Penguins, who find their soul mates through song, a penguin is born who cannot sing. But he can tap dance something fierce!

Name: Tenacious D in The Pick of Destiny
Directors_stars: ['Liam Lynch', 'Jack Black', 'Kyle Gass', 'JR Reed', 'Ronnie James Dio']
Information: To become the greatest band of all time, two slacker, wannabe-rockers set out on a quest to steal a legendary guitar pick that gives its holders incredible guitar skills, from a maximum security Rock and Roll museum.

Name: Scary Movie 4
Information: Cindy finds out the house she lives in is haunted by a little boy and goes on a quest to find out who killed him and why. Also, Alien "Tr-iPods" are invading the world and she has to uncover the secret in order to stop them.

Name: La science des rêves
Information: A man entranced by his dreams and imagination is love-struck with a French woman and feels he can show her his world.

Name: Superman Returns
Information: Superman returns to Earth after spending five years in space examining his homeworld Krypton. But he finds things have changed while he was gone, and he must once again prove himself important to the world.

Name: The Good Shepherd
Directors_stars: ['Robert De Niro', 'Matt Damon', 'Angelina Jolie', 'Robert De Niro', 'Alec Baldwin']
Information: The tumultuous early history of the Central Intelligence Agency is viewed through the prism of one man's life.

Name: Over the Hedge
Directors_stars: ['Tim Johnson', 'Karey Kirkpatrick', 'Bruce Willis', 'Garry Shandling', 'Steve Carell', 'Wanda Sykes']
Information: A scheming raccoon fools a mismatched family of forest creatures into helping him repay a debt of food, by invading the new suburban sprawl that popped up while they were hibernating...and learns a lesson about family himself.

Name: Mission: Impossible III
Directors_stars: ['J.J. Abrams', 'Tom Cruise', 'Michelle Monaghan', 'Ving Rhames', 'Philip Seymour Hoffman']
Information: IMF agent Ethan Hunt comes into conflict with a dangerous and sadistic arms dealer who threatens his life and his fiancée in response.

Name: Cars
Directors_stars: ['John Lasseter', 'Joe Ranft', 'Owen Wilson', 'Bonnie Hunt', 'Paul Newman', 'Larry the Cable Guy']
Information: A hot-shot race-car named Lightning McQueen gets waylaid in Radiator Springs, where he finds the true meaning of friendship and family.

Name: Children of Men
Information: In 2027, in a chaotic world in which women have become somehow infertile, a former activist agrees to help transport a miraculously pregnant woman to a sanctuary at sea.

Name: Babam ve Oglum
Information: The family of a left-wing journalist is torn apart after the military coup of Turkey in 1980.

Name: It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia
Information: Five friends with big egos and small brains are the proprietors of an Irish pub in Philadelphia.

Name: Supernatural
Information: Two brothers follow their father's footsteps as hunters, fighting evil supernatural beings of many kinds, including monsters, demons and gods that roam the earth.

Name: How I Met Your Mother
Information: A father recounts to his children - through a series of flashbacks - the journey he and his four best friends took leading up to him meeting their mother.

Name: Bones
Information: Forensic anthropologist Dr. Temperance "Bones" Brennan and cocky F.B.I. Special Agent Seeley Booth build a team to investigate murders. Quite often, there isn't more to examine than rotten flesh or mere bones.

Name: My Name Is Earl
Information: A ne'er do well wins $100,000 in the lottery and decides to right all the wrongs from his past with his newfound realization.

Name: Prison Break
Information: Due to a political conspiracy, an innocent man is sent to death row and his only hope is his brother, who makes it his mission to deliberately get himself sent to the same prison in order to break the both of them out, from the inside.
